# Laravel SMS Platform Backend Refactoring Walkthrough & Developer Guide

We have successfully refactored the Laravel SMS & school management platform into a clean, reusable, **API-First REST Backend**. The application now supports modern client applications (Web, Flutter, React Native, custom clients) while maintaining 100% compatibility with the existing Blade-based web system.

---

## 1. System Architecture & Routing Design

The refactored backend implements a clean separation of concerns, decoupling the delivery layer (REST API Controllers) from the database query and transaction layer (Repositories).

```mermaid
graph TD
    Client[Mobile / Web Client] -->|Tenant Domain Request| DNS[Route Resolver]
    DNS -->|tenant1.school.com| Bootstrap[bootstrap/app.php]
    Bootstrap -->|Tenancy Bootstrappers| Tenancy[Stancl Tenancy Middleware]
    Tenancy -->|Switches Database Connection| DBManager[Database Manager]
    DBManager -->|Loads Tenant Database| DB[(Tenant DB)]
    Tenancy -->|Applies Sanctum Guard| Sanctum[Sanctum Auth Middleware]
    Sanctum -->|Authenticates Tenant Token| API[routes/api.php]
    API -->|Dispatches Controller| Controllers[Api Controllers]
    Controllers -->|Invokes business actions| Repositories[Repositories app/Repositories]
    Repositories -->|Queries DB| DB
    Controllers -->|Formats Standard JSON| Client
```

### Multi-Tenancy Resolution
1. **Dynamic Database Connection**: We utilize Stancl Tenancy. When an API client requests `tenant1.yourdomain.com/api/v1/auth/login`, the `InitializeTenancyByDomain` middleware extracts the domain and automatically switches Laravel's default connection to that specific tenant's database.
2. **Personal Access Tokens Segregation**: Since the migrations for Laravel Sanctum's token table are run in the tenant database (`database/migrations/tenant/2024_05_31_134359_create_personal_access_tokens_table.php`), tokens are issued and validated against the tenant's own database. This ensures strict isolation and excellent security.

