## 3. Standardized Response Format

Every REST response follows a predictable, highly developer-friendly structure.

### Success Response (HTTP 200/211)
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "token": "3|zR45...token_content...",
    "user": {
      "id": "eOp9g8Y5aZ",
      "name": "JOHN DOE",
      "email": "john.doe@school.edu",
      "user_type": "admin"
    }
  },
  "message": "User logged in successfully."
}
```

### Error Response (HTTP 400/403/404)
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "User not found."
}
```

### Validation Error Response (HTTP 422)
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Validation Error.",
  "errors": {
    "name": [
      "The name field is required."
    ],
    "phone": [
      "The phone must start with a valid country code."
    ]
  }
}
```

