## 6. Maintenance, Upgrades, & Versioning

1. **API Versioning**: Currently registered under `/api/v1`. To make upgrades or breaking changes in the future, simply register a new route group `/api/v2` inside `bootstrap/app.php` and map it to a `v2` controllers subdirectory without affecting `v1` clients.
2. **Adding Custom Features**: When adding Vtus, digital utility payments, or other services, build a clean repository first (`app/Repositories/VtuRepo.php`), inject it into a dedicated API controller (`app/Http/Controllers/Api/ApiVtuController.php`), and register routes inside `routes/api.php`. This keeps the architecture pristine, modular, and 100% reusable across all future projects.
